RELATIONAL OPERATORS (How Sets Transform & Connect)
----------------------------------------------------

1. FIFTH-MOTION OPERATOR          Φ5(X) = perfect fifth above X
   (Core of functional harmony, Circle of Fifths, dominant resolution)
   Φ5(C) = G     Φ5⁻¹(C) = F
   Drives secondary dominants, circle progressions, key relationships.

2. MODE ROTATION OPERATOR         ρⁿ(Ionian) = nth rotated mode
   (Generates PMS from major scale)
   ρ¹ = Dorian, ρ² = Phrygian, ρ³ = Lydian, ρ⁴ = Mixolydian,
   ρ⁵ = Aeolian, ρ⁶ = Locrian.

3. PARALLEL BORROW OPERATOR       β(X) = borrowed parallel-minor version
   (Modal Interchange source)
   β(IV) = iv(Fm), β(I) = ♭III(Eb), etc. → feeds BCS.

4. APPLIED DOMINANT OPERATOR      Δ(X) = V7 of X
   (Temporary tonicization)
   Δ(V) = D7→G, Δ(ii) = A7→Dm, etc. → builds SDS.

5. TRITONE SUBSTITUTION OPERATOR  τ(V7) = dominant a tritone away
   (Chromatic reharmonization)
   τ(G7) = Db7 (shares 3rd/7th tritone) → links to TTP.

6. BACKDOOR RESOLUTION OPERATOR   Ω(T) = iv7–♭VII7–I path
   (Deceptive/soulful cadence via modal interchange)
   Ω(C) = Fm7–Bb7–Cmaj7.

